         </p>
         <p>The static bypass consists of the following main parts:<ul>
               <li>
                  <p>Thyristors (Q401)</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Static bypass controller (A401)</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Fan with fan monitoring (E401)</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
         <p>The static bypass provides the following functions:<ul>
               <li>
                  <p>Built-in PSU supplied from bypass mains input</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Dual speed fan supply for the static bypass fans (the fan speed
is controlled from the interface board via an input contact)</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Galvanically isolated thyristor drivers for the static bypass </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Snubber RC networks for the static bypass thyristors</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Output voltage measurement. If the UPS main controller or the
communication interface becomes inoperable, the board monitors the
system output phase-neutral voltage and independently enables the
static bypass if the output is lost</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Communication interface to the UPS controller</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Two signal outputs to indicate the state of the controller</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
